I"`<h2 class="section-heading">Salaries in IT</h2>
<p></p>

<p>The IT industry is very wide and broad. Even entry position salaries start at around $60.000 in the US. High-end jobs can range from $250.000 to $500.000 per year, but those jobs require many years of experience, certain certification, and other skills. If you're someone looking for a job in tech, be prepared to roll up your sleeves, and get to work!</p>

<h2 class="section-heading">1. Cloud Architect</h2>

<p>A cloud architect designs cloud networks. As cloud storage becomes more mainstream, it shouldn't be a suprise that this job position is becoming more and more in-demand. Some statistics suggest that some larger organizations may have up to 200 different cloud platforms, all of which need to be maintained, upgraded and kept in check. The average salary in the US for this position is $134.265 yearly.</p>

<h2 class="section-heading">2. Applications Architect</h2>

<p>Application architects, as the name suggests, specialize in designing, developing and maintaining specialized software for businesses and organizations. This job position provides plenty of opporutnities for problem-solving, as well as playing a key role in providing help to businesses in meeting their goals. This position is a level above an application developer, simply because they don't implement just the code, they're involved in the whole design proccess from start to finish. Almost everytime, an applications architect will be leading a team of application developers and engineers. As for the salary, the average income for this position in the US is $129.000.</p>

<h2 class="section-heading">3. IT Security Manager</h2>

<blockquote class="blockquote">“Information security and cyber security jobs are currently the best paying IT jobs in the market. The growing complexity, frequency, and intensity of cybersecurity risks make these roles an absolute necessity for all firms. Hence, there is a very high demand for skilled cyber and information security professionals, and this astronomical demand translates to higher pay for these individuals. Low supply of qualified professionals in these sectors to meet this great demand also contributes to the high salaries, perks, and benefits associated with these job roles as companies are constantly in competition with one another to attract the needed talent.”</blockquote>

<p>-Eric McGee, Senior Network Engineer at TRGDataCenters</p>

<p>Nowadays everything is digitalized, especially in the tech industry, and security threats are a big threat to organizations. This creates the need for IT security professionals, who will make sure everything is kept in tackt. This also creates a big demand for this job position, with an extremely well-paid salary. The biggest downside with this position is that you're always on, and you're likely to work long hours, sometimes during weekends and also nightshifts. Median salary in the US is $125.739.</p>

<h2 class="section-heading">4. AI Engineer</h2>

<p>AI and machine learning is the fastest-growing field in the IT industry. Just 10 years ago, AI required a lot of resources, thankfully the cloud takes care of that now. This creates a high demand for this position. AI Engineers are software developers and data scientists, working together to automate and improvte already existing technologies. Getting in this field will pay around $119.297.</p>

<h2 class="section-heading">5. Data Architect</h2>

<p>Data Architects jobs are hot in 2022 because of increase in the usage of the cloud. Cloud database administrators couldn't function without the help of Data Architects. Also Data architects find their cooperation with AI engineers, IT security managers as well as applications architects, to provide the necessary data for their work. Data Architects need to be able to "manipulate" with SQL and NoSQL databases, and dig deep into the fundamentals of statistics and discrete mathematics.</p>

<p><img class="img-fluid" src="https://www.usnews.com/object/image/00000179-327e-da49-a57f-f67e62e20000/210503-softwaredeveloper-stock.jpg?update-time=1620049889805&amp;size=responsive640" alt="Demo Image" /></p>

<h2 class="section-heading">6. Data Scientis</h2>

<p>Data scientists ususally don't have an IT background, but adapt pretty quickly in the IT field. They may not necessarily understand programming, but they can be extremely useful working with data-related programs, or data-oritented programming languages such as Python or R. They're usually very skilled in statistics, statistical analysis, data patterns and working with large data sets. A few years of experience in this field will get you rewarded with $117.212 yearly salary.</p>

<h2 class="section-heading">7. DevOps Engineer</h2>

<p>A DevOps engineer is an IT specialist  who specializes in implementing processes, tools and methodologies to balance the needs troughout the software development life cycle. Everything from development, maintenance and updates. DevOps have been around for quite a while, but recently they've got a surge in popularity. In 2022 being a DevOps engineer is one of the best paying jobs and is very likely to rise to the top of the IT jobs salaries. The current median salary for this position is a solid $105.107 in US.</p>

